-- Brasov Utility Awards Water Contract to Spanish Company
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-04-08T09:28:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-08/brasov-utility-awards-water-contract-to-spanish-company.html
Compania Apa Brasov SA , a Romanian
utility, awarded a 61.8 million-lei ($18 million) contract for
water infrastructure upgrades in the central city of Brasov to
the Spanish company Ocide Construccion SA.  The contract, initially estimated at 91.5 million lei,
includes works on a water pipeline linking Brasov and
neighboring Sacele, according to  a notice  on the European
Unionâ€™s tender website. The utility received 23 bids, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
